        "body": "This PR fixes the panic described in **#10639**, where the TUI renderer crashes when `col_wrap` calls `drawing_row_mut(...).unwrap()` on an invalid row during heavy scrolling/wrapping.\r\n\r\nThe fix safely handles cases where `drawing_row_mut` returns `None`, preventing the crash and allowing TUI updates to continue normally.\r\n\r\nRegression tests are included to ensure this scenario no longer panics.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## **### Testing Instructions**\r\n\r\n1. Check out the branch:\r\n\r\n```sh\r\ngit checkout fix-tui-crash\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Run tests:\r\n\r\n```sh\r\ncargo test -p turborepo-vt100\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. Verify:\r\n\r\n   * No panics occur during `col_wrap`\r\n   * Both new edge-case tests pass\r\n",
